title: The Moon Master
creator: Charles W. Diffin
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox recording of The Moon Master, by Charles W. Diffin. Read by Richard Kilmer. Through Infinite Deeps of Space Jerry Foster Hurtles to the Moon—Only to be Trapped by a Barbaric Race and Offered as a Living Sacrifice to Oong, their Loathsome, Hypnotic God. (Summary by Charles W. Diffin) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
